This paper is about object tracking, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves adapting the search area based on the predicted motion of the target, which requires some level of machine learning or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the method, which suggests that it involves some level of optimization or machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the method involves tracking a moving object, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves experiments on a benchmark dataset, which suggests that it may also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
